page.title: 01GENERAL DESCRIPTION
page.content: Most of our area is arable farmland.We have about{5}major farms,Pearson, Saul, Grant, Clements and Marshalls. We have three separate villages of which each has its own{church}and{Spar {shop.}The three villages are Butterwick,Benington and Leverton. In{Butterwick}there have been quite a few new houses built.Each village has 10 to 15 clubs,there is also a nursery.We also have a large drain called the{HOB HOLE}which flows into the sea.This part of the North sea is called The Wash.We have Freiston Shore,which is marshes, Benington shore and Butterwick Pullover.In our area there are no hills at all,it is very flat.In our fields there are many different crops such as;{wheat,barley,mustard and oil {seed rape.}
